reviews.review_text:
What's up? All these guys recordings sound dull?  Even his FOB, I know it's not the Schoeps because other Schoeps sources sound lively.

Great show, what a shame. 

Glad I downloaded the SBD in 2005 before Phil shut it down.

Just here to praise the taper. This tape sounds exactly like it did in front of the repeater stacks on the lawn that night, and I know this because I was standing on the lawn right next to the section that night, losing my %#$^@%. 

The characterization of Ted's recordings as "dull" is not one endorsed by this Schoeps taper, or any of the numerous other Schoeps tapers I know for that matter.  Indeed, Ted Mattes and his crew are pretty much legends and trailbreakers to us.  Here's to you, Ted!  Thanks for getting it done.
